<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1505,1745]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,214,1506,1530]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Note.</emphasis>
The four juvenile 
<typeStatus box="[427,525,1506,1530]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">syntypes</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[540,641,1505,1529]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,207,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,195,1917]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Nilus spp., habitus (1, 3, 5, 8 dorsal view; 2, 4, 6, 9 ventral view; 7, 10 frontal view). 1 – 7 Nilus curtus O. Pickard-Cambridge 1876, juvenile syntypes from Egypt. 8 – 10 Nilus oblongus Pavesi 1897, holotype, immature female, from Ethiopia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278845/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs 
<number box="[599,641,1505,1529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="4.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="1.0">1–7</number>
</figureCitation>
) are clearly congeneric with 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1093,1505,1529]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Thalassius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[973,1093,1505,1529]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Thalassius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (Sierwald, in litt.). Comparisons with juvenile 
<taxonomicName box="[409,535,1541,1565]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Dolomedes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[409,535,1541,1565]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Dolomedes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[550,670,1541,1565]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Thalassius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[550,670,1541,1565]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Thalassius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other 
<taxonomicName box="[793,910,1541,1565]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pisauridae</taxonomicName>
during the present study supported this result. The eye arrangement, with the anterior eye row distinctly wider than posterior median eyes, and the colour pattern, especially with narrow lateral bands on dorsal prosoma, were congruent with other congenerics. The species identity cannot be resolved by morphology, but 
<taxonomicName box="[643,830,1650,1673]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Thalassius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosissimus">
<emphasis box="[643,830,1650,1673]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">N. spinosissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species of the genus occurring in northern Africa and in 
<collectingCountry box="[304,371,1686,1710]" name="Egypt" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Egypt</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sierwald" box="[385,624,1685,1709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Sierwald, P. (1987) Revision der Gattung Thalassius (Arachnida, Araneae, Pisauridae). Verhandlungen des naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins Hamburg, 29, 51 - 142." type="journal article" year="1987">
Sierwald 
<number box="[492,552,1685,1709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1987.0">1987</number>
: 
<number box="[563,591,1686,1709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="77.0">77</number>
ff.
</bibRefCitation>
) and therefore 
<taxonomicName box="[793,895,1686,1709]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Nilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtus">
<emphasis box="[793,895,1686,1709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">N. curtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here proposed as senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Thalassius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosissimus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">N. spinosissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
